1
00:00:39,780 --> 00:00:41,950
I forgot how she looked.

2
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:47,320
Did she look like this?

3
00:00:50,289 --> 00:00:51,359
Like this?

4
00:00:53,390 --> 00:00:54,390
Or...

5
00:00:55,390 --> 00:00:56,390
like this?

6
00:01:16,450 --> 00:01:19,879
I wonder what she looks like.

7
00:01:22,319 --> 00:01:26,930
I wanted to draw a face,
but I unconsciously drew a circle.

8
00:01:26,930 --> 00:01:27,930
(Episode 4: I Wanted to Draw a Face,
but I Unconsciously Drew a Circle)

9
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:29,459
Nice to meet you.

10
00:01:29,689 --> 00:01:30,730
Nice to meet you.

11
00:01:30,730 --> 00:01:32,200
I am...

12
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:34,599
- I'm Veronica Park.
- Veronica Park.

13
00:01:58,390 --> 00:02:00,359
Does she not like the food?

14
00:02:00,989 --> 00:02:02,930
I can't lose points already.

15
00:02:02,930 --> 00:02:04,129
My gosh.

16
00:02:05,530 --> 00:02:07,069
Do you not like the food?

17
00:02:07,129 --> 00:02:08,199
What are you talking about?

18
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:09,930
My stomach is all excited...

19
00:02:10,569 --> 00:02:11,569
Pardon?

20
00:02:14,439 --> 00:02:17,810
My stomach feels very comfortable.

21
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:19,639
It's what I eat all the time.

22
00:02:20,139 --> 00:02:21,379
That's a relief.

23
00:02:22,879 --> 00:02:25,620
I didn't know
what kind of wine you'd like.

24
00:02:27,289 --> 00:02:28,750
I picked one
based on my own taste.

25
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:31,289
Armand de Brignac Blanc de Blancs.

26
00:02:31,819 --> 00:02:32,889
You know very well.

27
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:35,560
Of course, I know.
I'm the one who ordered that.

28
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,759
It's quite affordable.

29
00:02:37,759 --> 00:02:39,360
It's a 1,500-dollar wine.

30
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,599
And it has a very clean aftertaste.

31
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:42,669
I hope it's right.

32
00:02:42,669 --> 00:02:44,969
I also enjoy it very often.

33
00:02:45,370 --> 00:02:48,139
It's more like
I enjoyed ordering it often...

34
00:02:48,139 --> 00:02:49,770
so you could drink it.

35
00:02:52,139 --> 00:02:53,210
I see.

36
00:03:07,159 --> 00:03:09,360
Should we clink glasses first?

37
00:03:10,629 --> 00:03:11,759
Cheers to what?

38
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:15,629
Cheers to our first rendezvous.

39
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:19,000
"First rendezvous"?

40
00:03:28,409 --> 00:03:30,009
She should've made a debut
as a girl group member.

41
00:03:30,009 --> 00:03:31,379
I can't believe
she's stuck in an office.

42
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:33,620
Leave her be.

43
00:03:33,889 --> 00:03:35,789
She's always quiet at work
because she walks on eggshells...

44
00:03:35,789 --> 00:03:38,189
around her boss.
Imagine how stressed she must be.

45
00:03:50,699 --> 00:03:51,800
Listen to me carefully, Ha Ni.

46
00:03:52,539 --> 00:03:54,639
I don't want to get you involved
in anything.

47
00:03:55,009 --> 00:03:57,310
So don't ever greet me
like you know me.

48
00:03:57,509 --> 00:03:58,939
And regardless of
what I end up doing,

49
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,680
you must pretend
like you don't know anything.

50
00:04:02,650 --> 00:04:04,750
Even if someone in this company
ends up dying.

51
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:11,120
No, no.

52
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:13,189
Hey, ladies!

53
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:18,329
Hey!

54
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,199
You said you'll be here in
15 minutes, but it took you 2 hours.

55
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,769
Gosh, I'm really sorry.

56
00:04:23,769 --> 00:04:25,370
I had to take care of something.

57
00:04:26,170 --> 00:04:28,269
By the way, where's Gal Hee?

58
00:04:28,269 --> 00:04:30,779
She left after she got a phone call,
and we can't even reach her.

59
00:04:30,779 --> 00:04:33,209
I'm worried that she might've left
without even paying.

60
00:04:33,509 --> 00:04:35,050
You guys should be
more understanding.

61
00:04:35,050 --> 00:04:37,420
I'm pretty sure she's busy
slaving away for her boss.

62
00:04:37,779 --> 00:04:39,079
You should feel sorry for her.

63
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:44,790
I'm sorry, but can you
pick that up for me?

64
00:04:45,759 --> 00:04:48,160
I'm sure you already know this,
but I never...

65
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:51,759
had to bend down in front of anyone
in my entire life.

66
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:56,470
The rumors were right.
She really is an annoying brat.

67
00:04:58,839 --> 00:05:00,769
Yes, of course.
I'll pick it up for you.

68
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:02,639
Excuse me.

69
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:07,110
Thank you.

70
00:05:14,620 --> 00:05:15,649
My goodness.

71
00:05:16,389 --> 00:05:20,529
Can you wipe this off for me too?

72
00:05:20,660 --> 00:05:24,899
I'm sure you already know this,
but I never...

73
00:05:25,259 --> 00:05:27,730
had to do anything myself
during my entire life.

74
00:05:51,959 --> 00:05:52,990
Are you okay now?

75
00:06:13,910 --> 00:06:17,519
No way. Is this peanut?

76
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:20,920
Spit it out.

77
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:22,790
Did you spit everything out?

78
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:25,060
You should rinse your mouth. Hurry.

79
00:06:25,060 --> 00:06:26,060
Okay.

80
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,699
What... What's the matter?

81
00:06:31,699 --> 00:06:32,829
It's peanut.

82
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:37,370
They said it'll be garlic sauce.
Why did they serve peanut sauce?

83
00:06:39,639 --> 00:06:41,769
Is there sauce on your mouth?

84
00:06:41,769 --> 00:06:44,680
Do you have a rash?
Are you burning up?

85
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,740
I'm okay, but you...

86
00:06:46,579 --> 00:06:49,050
caught it with your hand.

87
00:06:56,449 --> 00:06:58,689
I can't believe myself.

88
00:06:58,689 --> 00:07:00,629
It's as if I'm destined to be
a minion...

89
00:07:00,629 --> 00:07:02,589
regardless of
whatever situation I'm in.

90
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:08,899
Why did I catch the food
he was eating with my hand?

91
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:13,540
A conglomerate's daughter
would never do something like that.

92
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:19,040
Secretary Jeong.

93
00:07:19,339 --> 00:07:21,810
You just had a meal
you'll never be able to afford.

94
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:24,879
Now, let's wrap things up
and call it a night...

95
00:07:24,879 --> 00:07:28,220
before your boss begins
to get suspicious of you.

96
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:40,100
What was that?
Is she just being fake?

97
00:07:41,769 --> 00:07:43,300
I can't believe she caught
what I was eating with her hand.

98
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:04,490
Are you okay?

99
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:07,360
No problem.

100
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:10,459
By the way, how did you know
that I'm allergic...

101
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:12,230
to peanuts?

102
00:08:12,529 --> 00:08:13,529
What?

103
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:18,399
Your secretary.

104
00:08:19,470 --> 00:08:22,509
Your secretary told me...

105
00:08:22,509 --> 00:08:25,579
when I talked to her over the phone
regarding our rendezvous.

106
00:08:25,579 --> 00:08:28,110
- Oh, Secretary Jeong?
- Yes.

107
00:08:29,579 --> 00:08:31,180
Should we go now?

108
00:08:31,180 --> 00:08:34,120
Wait. I'll ask them
to have your car ready.

109
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:35,750
- What's your license plate number?
- What?

110
00:08:37,620 --> 00:08:39,490
Well, my car...

111
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:43,129
I do have a car.

112
00:08:43,129 --> 00:08:46,559
But I thought I might have
a few drinks,

113
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,100
so I didn't drive here.

114
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,240
Don't you have a driver?

115
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,740
What? A driver?

116
00:08:53,570 --> 00:08:54,610
Yes, I have one.

117
00:08:55,509 --> 00:08:56,570
I do have a driver.

118
00:08:57,879 --> 00:08:59,110
But I sent him on vacation.

119
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:01,210
He hasn't been able to rest
for a long time.

120
00:09:02,110 --> 00:09:04,750
Then I shouldn't have told
my driver to leave.

121
00:09:05,220 --> 00:09:09,450
Actually, this hotel provides
a limousine service.

122
00:09:09,450 --> 00:09:10,450
No.

123
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,690
I didn't know that.

124
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:15,129
I'll just walk home.

125
00:09:15,429 --> 00:09:16,929
- You're going to walk?
- Yes.

126
00:09:17,429 --> 00:09:19,399
I heard it's going to rain soon.

127
00:09:19,799 --> 00:09:22,799
Well, the thing is,
I must've eaten way too fast.

128
00:09:24,039 --> 00:09:25,700
I feel a little bloated.

129
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:28,710
When will I ever get a chance
to walk...

130
00:09:29,039 --> 00:09:31,379
if not today?

131
00:09:32,779 --> 00:09:34,779
- Then I'll walk with you.
- What?

132
00:09:35,049 --> 00:09:38,250
I was also feeling
a little bloated myself.

133
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:39,950
Let's go.

134
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:01,769
Why would you need
something like this?

135
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:04,340
When it comes to people like us,
our parents are our business cards.

136
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:06,779
- Who's your father?
- I don't know.

137
00:10:07,450 --> 00:10:09,279
I never had a father.

138
00:10:09,279 --> 00:10:11,220
My mom raised me all by herself.

139
00:10:11,220 --> 00:10:13,120
Then who's your mother?

140
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:15,789
Back when she was alive,
she used to work at TnT Mobile...

141
00:10:15,789 --> 00:10:17,250
as Chairman Do's secretary.

142
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:18,990
And she passed away
when I was a senior in high school.

143
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:23,629
Then your grandfather must've been
someone very impressive.

144
00:10:23,629 --> 00:10:26,200
Yes, he was a very impressive man.

145
00:10:27,129 --> 00:10:29,399
He was a farmer
who grew chili peppers,

146
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,470
and he managed to send
all his six children to college.

147
00:10:31,669 --> 00:10:32,840
Chili peppers?

148
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:34,169
What's wrong?

149
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,409
Do you not like my business card?

150
00:10:36,570 --> 00:10:37,840
Don't worry.

151
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:40,309
If your business card is lame,
I'll find something from your face.

152
00:10:40,309 --> 00:10:42,580
If your face is lousy,
I'll find something from your body.

153
00:10:42,610 --> 00:10:45,149
I manage to find out any charm
a man may hold no matter what.

154
00:10:45,149 --> 00:10:47,750
I have such an amazing talent,
you see.

155
00:10:47,850 --> 00:10:50,220
Still, I want you
to like me for my business card.

156
00:10:50,350 --> 00:10:52,559
I turned out pretty well
growing up without a dad.

157
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:55,730
And I lived tenaciously
even after my mom died.

158
00:10:56,090 --> 00:10:57,830
The country's overall household debt
is 140 million dollars,

159
00:10:57,830 --> 00:10:59,399
but I'm free from debt
and have a great job.

160
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:02,529
Isn't my business card good enough?

161
00:11:03,070 --> 00:11:06,970
Don't you think
President Sim Hae Yong should...

162
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:08,669
get some credit
for your business card?

163
00:11:09,009 --> 00:11:12,340
He set me up with you
instead of his own nephew.

164
00:11:12,809 --> 00:11:15,149
I guess it's a bigger deal
worth more than a designer bag.

165
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:23,450
("Is YK Mobile Getting
the Exclusive Run of Cinepark?")

166
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,620
Why don't you work on that?

167
00:11:26,889 --> 00:11:27,960
Me?

168
00:11:28,090 --> 00:11:30,429
If you want the Media divisions
to be combined successfully,

169
00:11:34,330 --> 00:11:36,100
you'll have to make
some contribution.

170
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,909
This is the project proposal
for the exclusive run of Cinepark.

171
00:11:43,409 --> 00:11:45,610
Too bad.

172
00:11:46,139 --> 00:11:48,610
I don't meet people after six.

173
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:50,350
I only meet guys.

174
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:52,250
Then I'll visit you
before six sometime.

175
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,549
As a person.

176
00:11:53,549 --> 00:11:55,850
Why don't we have
some drinks now instead?

177
00:11:56,190 --> 00:11:57,220
As a guy.

178
00:11:57,220 --> 00:11:59,120
- I can't.
- Why not?

179
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:02,490
I'm paying for this
with the company credit card.

180
00:12:02,929 --> 00:12:05,659
I'm not supposed to drink
with the company's money.

181
00:12:06,830 --> 00:12:11,269
Then I'll buy our drinks, baby.

182
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:13,070
Water is fine.

183
00:12:17,269 --> 00:12:20,639
Don't you think
I'm doing this for a reason?

184
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:22,679
Don't you think...

185
00:12:24,419 --> 00:12:26,649
you might ruin everything
by acting like that?

186
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,820
- I don't.
- Why not?

187
00:12:29,019 --> 00:12:30,720
I heard you are quite unique,

188
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:33,259
but I believe you have
your own standards.

189
00:12:34,759 --> 00:12:37,529
Even in a movie made with
a lot of money and good actors,

190
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:39,899
you sort out the flaws in the film.

191
00:12:39,899 --> 00:12:42,330
And even in a low-budget movie
of an unknown director,

192
00:12:42,429 --> 00:12:45,769
you find out
its strength and merits.

193
00:12:46,070 --> 00:12:47,940
You're truly worth being called
the Master of Movie Success.

194
00:12:48,269 --> 00:12:51,710
I almost grinned hearing that.

195
00:12:52,379 --> 00:12:55,350
- Pardon?
- I don't believe in papers.

196
00:12:55,610 --> 00:12:56,750
I only believe in money.

197
00:12:58,649 --> 00:13:01,350
I'll read it. If it's trash,
I'll throw it out.

198
00:13:01,350 --> 00:13:03,519
If it seems lucrative,
I'll give you a call.

199
00:13:04,049 --> 00:13:05,120
All right then.

200
00:13:24,379 --> 00:13:27,240
What's going on?
How much longer do I have to walk?

201
00:13:28,409 --> 00:13:30,850
What if he walks to my place?

202
00:13:42,759 --> 00:13:43,929
It's raining.

203
00:13:57,710 --> 00:13:58,980
Why are you...

204
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:00,909
What?

205
00:14:08,250 --> 00:14:11,659
Give me that. I'm a man.
I should hold it.

206
00:14:51,259 --> 00:14:52,259
How's your stomach?

207
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:56,070
You said you were feeling bloated.
How do you feel now?

208
00:14:57,129 --> 00:14:59,370
Maybe it's because I skipped lunch?

209
00:15:00,470 --> 00:15:02,769
I often have indigestion
after dinner these days.

210
00:15:04,639 --> 00:15:06,440
You skipped lunch? Why?

211
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:10,549
My secretary usually gets me lunch,

212
00:15:10,549 --> 00:15:12,820
and I eat it in my office.

213
00:15:14,179 --> 00:15:17,190
But she was out
during the lunch hour today.

214
00:15:19,519 --> 00:15:20,519
Well...

215
00:15:21,129 --> 00:15:23,460
You can't even have lunch
without your secretary?

216
00:15:23,629 --> 00:15:27,399
You could go to the cafeteria
or restaurants in the neighborhood.

217
00:15:28,230 --> 00:15:30,129
I know. But...

218
00:15:31,669 --> 00:15:35,240
Eating lunch looking
at people's faces is...

219
00:15:38,210 --> 00:15:39,240
I'm a little tired of it.

220
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:42,950
Oh, I see.

221
00:15:46,350 --> 00:15:48,919
You should press here.

222
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:52,690
My mom used to do it
for indigestion when I was young.

223
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:56,490
Chairman Park Seok Ja did?

224
00:16:00,659 --> 00:16:03,370
My mom is indeed a chairman.

225
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,940
So... Like this?

226
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,409
No. Look.

227
00:16:13,610 --> 00:16:15,409
From inside. Press it hard.

228
00:16:18,279 --> 00:16:21,419
My mom used to chant...

229
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:23,649
some weird spell doing this.

230
00:16:27,389 --> 00:16:29,429
Go down. Go down.

231
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:32,559
It shall go down
as if there's oil in it.

232
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:34,970
Stop bothering my girl...

233
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:37,769
and go down immediately.

234
00:16:40,669 --> 00:16:41,769
It came out!

235
00:16:42,269 --> 00:16:44,169
Well... Excuse me.

236
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:47,779
I guess it's working.
Let me do it again.

237
00:17:00,990 --> 00:17:02,289
I wonder...

238
00:17:03,259 --> 00:17:05,160
what she looks like.

239
00:17:14,170 --> 00:17:16,569
Why are you staring at me like that?

240
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,740
Well... Nothing.

241
00:17:20,309 --> 00:17:23,680
You're just different
from what I expected.

242
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:30,789
I mean, it's raining now.

243
00:17:31,519 --> 00:17:32,759
Shall we go now?

244
00:17:34,119 --> 00:17:35,190
Taxi.

245
00:17:39,099 --> 00:17:40,500
I'll take you home.

246
00:17:40,930 --> 00:17:42,769
No, no.

247
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:46,900
I don't like to owe anyone.

248
00:17:58,950 --> 00:18:00,119
Mr. Do Min Ik.

249
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:01,819
Yes?

250
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:03,589
It was...

251
00:18:04,990 --> 00:18:06,220
nice meeting you.

252
00:18:07,359 --> 00:18:10,289
And I'm sorry.

253
00:18:11,029 --> 00:18:13,230
I'm the one who should apologize.

254
00:18:43,759 --> 00:18:45,000
What did he say?

255
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:48,869
Chairman Park.

256
00:18:49,430 --> 00:18:51,869
You're reaching the climax
without an intro again.

257
00:18:52,099 --> 00:18:55,440
Aren't you supposed
to say hello to me first?

258
00:18:55,539 --> 00:18:58,579
I just can't wait.
I don't care about the intro.

259
00:18:58,579 --> 00:19:00,079
Saying hello, my foot.

260
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:05,680
You heard that
they met last night, right?

261
00:19:06,779 --> 00:19:08,619
What did your daughter say?

262
00:19:09,589 --> 00:19:13,019
Her nickname is Suction Pump.
I don't care what she says.

263
00:19:13,259 --> 00:19:15,930
What matters is
what your son said.

264
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:22,369
Well... More than he thought,
your daughter was...

265
00:19:25,140 --> 00:19:26,269
She was nice.

266
00:19:31,940 --> 00:19:33,039
What?

267
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:52,099
It's okay, Jeong Gal Hee.

268
00:19:52,829 --> 00:19:55,400
Just think that it was just
a novel and forget about it.

269
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:57,400
Just think that it was a dream.

270
00:19:57,599 --> 00:20:00,140
Forget all about it.

271
00:20:00,569 --> 00:20:01,609
Gosh.

272
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:07,539
Why did I do that?
I must've been crazy.

273
00:20:07,539 --> 00:20:08,680
Really crazy!

274
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:12,220
How am I going to see his face?

275
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:15,119
I can't believe this. My gosh.

276
00:20:17,519 --> 00:20:18,789
What do you want to forget?

277
00:20:19,789 --> 00:20:21,490
Did you have a nightmare last night?

278
00:20:22,490 --> 00:20:24,460
Why did you come so early?

279
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:26,630
You didn't have coffee yet, right?

280
00:20:29,470 --> 00:20:30,529
I did.

281
00:20:30,829 --> 00:20:33,240
Because you don't get me coffee
before office hours.

282
00:20:34,099 --> 00:20:36,170
- What about your shoes?
- I polished them already.

283
00:20:36,869 --> 00:20:40,539
You said you didn't take personal
orders that are not work-related.

284
00:20:41,609 --> 00:20:43,549
Did you feed the fish?
Did you water the plants?

285
00:20:43,549 --> 00:20:46,220
Please let me do something.

286
00:20:49,519 --> 00:20:50,519
Well...

287
00:20:51,089 --> 00:20:53,519
I think the light in my room
went out.

288
00:20:53,519 --> 00:20:57,089
Okay. I will go buy a new one
right away.

289
00:21:02,869 --> 00:21:03,970
Secretary Jeong.

290
00:21:05,099 --> 00:21:06,170
Yes.

291
00:21:06,369 --> 00:21:10,009
I know that you don't want
to see my face.

292
00:21:10,569 --> 00:21:14,309
But I would like you
to look at my face when you work.

293
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:15,809
Okay.

294
00:21:15,809 --> 00:21:17,549
Unfortunately,

295
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:20,720
you're the only one I can see.

296
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,990
Okay.

297
00:21:27,789 --> 00:21:28,829
(Veronica Park)

298
00:21:29,589 --> 00:21:30,890
See you!

299
00:21:39,869 --> 00:21:41,200
Hello.

300
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:42,569
Hello.

301
00:21:43,940 --> 00:21:45,039
It's me.

302
00:21:45,809 --> 00:21:47,009
This reminds me of the old days.

303
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,250
If you had a fun night,

304
00:21:50,250 --> 00:21:52,319
it's time to match our alibis.

305
00:21:53,319 --> 00:21:56,390
I hope you did your share
for no consequences, right?

306
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:57,789
It's right up your alley.

307
00:21:58,819 --> 00:21:59,819
Well...

308
00:22:00,690 --> 00:22:04,859
It looks like the appointment was
arranged by both your mothers.

309
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:08,170
If we told them
you did not show up at all,

310
00:22:08,329 --> 00:22:09,799
it would have upset the chairman,

311
00:22:09,799 --> 00:22:12,970
and my boss would have thought
he got stood up.

312
00:22:12,970 --> 00:22:15,539
That's why I couldn't tell them so.

313
00:22:16,940 --> 00:22:18,079
So?

314
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:21,710
So, I thought...

315
00:22:21,710 --> 00:22:25,579
maybe I should ask
for my boss' understanding...

316
00:22:26,250 --> 00:22:29,049
and tell them
that you met each other.

317
00:22:33,059 --> 00:22:36,690
So you told them I was there.

318
00:22:36,890 --> 00:22:37,890
Yes.

319
00:22:38,259 --> 00:22:41,829
I told them
you actually met each other.

320
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,640
Hello?

321
00:22:51,809 --> 00:22:53,440
Well done.

322
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:55,980
Then I should tell my family
the same.

323
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:57,250
Just give me...

324
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,819
that man's phone number.

325
00:23:00,819 --> 00:23:01,819
What?

326
00:23:03,619 --> 00:23:05,920
Why do you want
my boss' phone number?

327
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:08,259
I didn't mean your boss.

328
00:23:11,799 --> 00:23:13,799
(Project Proposal, TnT Mobile)

329
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:18,140
Doesn't this place
remind you of the old days?

330
00:23:20,069 --> 00:23:21,869
I used to come here on my payday.

331
00:23:22,210 --> 00:23:25,279
Back when your mother and I worked
for Chairman Do Wan Bae.

332
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:28,150
I remember the time.

333
00:23:28,549 --> 00:23:31,450
After my mother passed away,
I had no money to go study abroad.

334
00:23:31,619 --> 00:23:34,319
But then Chairman Do paid
the tuition for me.

335
00:23:34,319 --> 00:23:37,390
You and I came here, ordered a lot
of pork cutlets, and celebrated it.

336
00:23:37,390 --> 00:23:38,990
I can't forget that day.

337
00:23:38,990 --> 00:23:40,190
Because of you...

338
00:23:42,230 --> 00:23:43,789
Because of me, what?

339
00:23:44,529 --> 00:23:46,900
Because of you, I was so happy.

340
00:23:51,569 --> 00:23:53,440
- Dae Ju.
- Yes, Eul Wang.

341
00:23:54,039 --> 00:23:55,109
You know,

342
00:23:55,470 --> 00:23:58,480
no matter what happens,
I'm on your side.

343
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:01,240
And no matter what happens,
you're on my side.

344
00:24:13,789 --> 00:24:15,089
Why is this here?

345
00:24:20,430 --> 00:24:21,460
Goodness.

346
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:27,799
I thought I lost it. Maybe I didn't.

347
00:24:31,009 --> 00:24:32,779
(Romi, the Licking Dog)

348
00:24:36,779 --> 00:24:37,809
But I lost it.

349
00:24:41,180 --> 00:24:42,589
What happened?

350
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:48,460
You're back early.

351
00:24:48,890 --> 00:24:50,390
Yes. Hey.

352
00:24:51,799 --> 00:24:52,900
Why is this here?

353
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:54,400
What? The USB stick?

354
00:24:55,099 --> 00:24:56,630
You gave it to me
and said I should watch it.

355
00:24:56,630 --> 00:24:58,640
You said the dog looked
just like the dog we had.

356
00:25:00,970 --> 00:25:02,039
Why?

357
00:25:02,210 --> 00:25:03,309
Never mind.

358
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,579
Hey, let's not get distracted
by other things today.

359
00:25:08,450 --> 00:25:11,180
I'd like to hear
your precious secret.

360
00:25:19,190 --> 00:25:21,289
- Min Ik.
- Yes.

361
00:25:23,259 --> 00:25:24,630
I'm quitting the company.

362
00:25:25,799 --> 00:25:27,829
Why do you talk nonsense
with such a serious face?

363
00:25:30,130 --> 00:25:33,900
I wanted to tell you first
before I hand in my resignation.

364
00:25:37,569 --> 00:25:39,339
I'll be working
only until the next month.

365
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:41,710
Why?

366
00:25:43,549 --> 00:25:44,579
Why?

367
00:25:45,819 --> 00:25:47,180
The world is a big place.

368
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:50,250
I can go to the Maldives
and have a glass of mojito.

369
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:53,519
I can film a road movie
with a strange woman.

370
00:25:56,089 --> 00:25:57,089
No, you can't.

371
00:26:02,470 --> 00:26:03,470
Min Ik.

372
00:26:03,470 --> 00:26:06,569
You have been with me
for over 20 years since we were 7.

373
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,109
You can't just hand in a resignation
without discussing it with me.

374
00:26:09,109 --> 00:26:10,170
I won't let you.

375
00:26:11,109 --> 00:26:13,740
I have been with you for 27 years
since we were 7.

376
00:26:13,740 --> 00:26:15,680
Don't you think it's time for us
to go separate ways?

377
00:26:16,180 --> 00:26:19,079
No. I need you.
I'm putting my foot down.

378
00:26:19,279 --> 00:26:21,150
End of conversation. See you.

379
00:26:21,819 --> 00:26:23,890
Until when do I have to stay
as your minion?

380
00:26:31,029 --> 00:26:32,059
Excuse me?

381
00:26:33,130 --> 00:26:34,400
Please let me go, Min Ik.

382
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:38,400
That's the only way you'll live.

383
00:27:13,470 --> 00:27:14,970
The light is still out.

384
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:18,410
She said she would call
the technicians.

385
00:27:36,059 --> 00:27:37,289
Yes, come in.

386
00:27:42,599 --> 00:27:43,730
What brings you here?

387
00:27:43,730 --> 00:27:46,339
You left this in the car.

388
00:27:46,339 --> 00:27:48,299
Oh, right. Thank you.

389
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:55,279
Why did you not turn the light on?

390
00:27:56,549 --> 00:27:59,720
I think the light went off.
It won't turn on.

391
00:28:01,519 --> 00:28:03,119
You can leave now.

392
00:28:03,490 --> 00:28:04,750
I can go home by myself.

393
00:28:06,390 --> 00:28:09,059
Okay, then.

394
00:28:11,529 --> 00:28:12,630
Thank you.

395
00:28:14,029 --> 00:28:19,470
100 dollars, 110 dollars,
120 dollars...

396
00:28:20,539 --> 00:28:22,470
Here's more.

397
00:28:24,809 --> 00:28:29,549
I see you're charging me
the parking fee as well.

398
00:28:30,509 --> 00:28:33,319
You're lucky we're not charging you
for the clothes...

399
00:28:33,319 --> 00:28:34,819
and the hairdo we did for you.

400
00:28:37,390 --> 00:28:39,789
I'm sorry about
what happened yesterday.

401
00:28:46,900 --> 00:28:49,500
Let's go. Let's eat some jokbal
with this money.

402
00:28:50,930 --> 00:28:53,569
I'll catch up with you.
I need to bring my office bag.

403
00:29:40,450 --> 00:29:42,019
The car key.

404
00:30:04,970 --> 00:30:06,079
Who are you?

405
00:30:26,799 --> 00:30:27,859
Is that...

406
00:30:29,170 --> 00:30:30,170
you?

407
00:30:32,670 --> 00:30:33,740
It's you, isn't it?

408
00:30:34,869 --> 00:30:36,509
How did you get in here?

409
00:30:50,289 --> 00:30:51,849
- Who are you?
- No!

410
00:30:55,559 --> 00:30:57,359
Secretary Jeong, this is the man.

411
00:30:57,660 --> 00:31:00,599
This man is the man
who tried to kill me.

412
00:31:00,599 --> 00:31:01,930
Sir, please put it back.

413
00:31:02,269 --> 00:31:04,130
It's your driver.

414
00:31:04,630 --> 00:31:05,700
What?

415
00:31:10,769 --> 00:31:12,710
But...

416
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:14,680
This cap...

417
00:31:15,650 --> 00:31:16,650
and the box cutter.

418
00:31:16,650 --> 00:31:17,779
It's just a common box cutter.

419
00:31:18,049 --> 00:31:21,150
Everyone has one
in their desk drawer.

420
00:31:23,150 --> 00:31:24,150
But he is...

421
00:31:36,529 --> 00:31:37,599
Are you okay?

422
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:41,599
I'm okay.

423
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:43,410
Did you get hurt?

424
00:31:43,410 --> 00:31:44,509
But...

425
00:31:45,309 --> 00:31:46,480
what were you doing...

426
00:31:47,839 --> 00:31:49,579
in my room?

427
00:31:50,450 --> 00:31:53,680
I said you could leave earlier.

428
00:31:55,049 --> 00:31:56,119
Because of the light.

429
00:31:56,390 --> 00:31:59,359
It looked like
the light was troubling you.

430
00:32:00,289 --> 00:32:02,529
I know how to fix lights,

431
00:32:03,029 --> 00:32:04,359
so I was trying to fix it.

432
00:32:04,759 --> 00:32:07,529
But why did you
not answer me earlier?

433
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:14,339
Sir, it's blood!

434
00:32:14,599 --> 00:32:15,809
It's blood!

435
00:32:30,319 --> 00:32:32,089
- 9 times 9 equals?
- 81.

436
00:32:32,190 --> 00:32:34,019
- 2 times 9 equals?
- 18!

437
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:35,960
Am I doing the CT scan?

438
00:32:36,789 --> 00:32:39,960
You don't need a CT scan for
a tiny scratch from a box cutter.

439
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:41,730
You should know you're lucky
that we had an extra patient room.

440
00:32:41,829 --> 00:32:44,170
Then give me some medications
and fix it.

441
00:32:45,700 --> 00:32:48,710
I almost killed my driver.

442
00:32:48,910 --> 00:32:51,740
Are you going to send me
some tofu...

443
00:32:51,740 --> 00:32:53,180
when I go to a prison?

444
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:55,349
Do you still not see anyone?

445
00:32:58,609 --> 00:32:59,750
I still can see...

446
00:33:00,950 --> 00:33:02,390
only one person.

447
00:33:04,420 --> 00:33:05,490
That's all I can see.

448
00:33:06,519 --> 00:33:08,319
Take a good rest today.

449
00:33:08,690 --> 00:33:11,230
Dr. Park finally arrived
from the United States,

450
00:33:11,230 --> 00:33:13,000
so you can see him tomorrow
before you leave.

451
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:14,559
Make sure you have someone
to nurse you.

452
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:18,900
There comes the person.

453
00:33:18,900 --> 00:33:20,000
Hi.

454
00:33:20,700 --> 00:33:22,269
That's person who will nurse me.

455
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,339
You should ask the police
for help again.

456
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:29,910
You've become too sensitive because
you couldn't catch the criminal.

457
00:33:29,910 --> 00:33:31,279
That's why this all happened.

458
00:33:31,380 --> 00:33:32,549
I know.

459
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:35,220
Excuse me.

460
00:33:36,950 --> 00:33:38,089
Mr. Eun.

461
00:33:40,089 --> 00:33:42,890
How do you feel?

462
00:33:52,869 --> 00:33:53,869
Well...

463
00:33:56,569 --> 00:33:59,509
I'm sorry about
what happened earlier.

464
00:34:04,180 --> 00:34:06,579
It's okay.
I also didn't recognize you...

465
00:34:06,579 --> 00:34:08,280
because it was dark.

466
00:34:09,449 --> 00:34:13,119
Thank you for your understanding.

467
00:34:17,659 --> 00:34:19,000
Then I wish you take a good rest.

468
00:34:19,530 --> 00:34:21,500
Feel free to call me
whenever you need me.

469
00:34:52,159 --> 00:34:53,360
I found it, boss.

470
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,599
Do you feel all right?

471
00:35:00,070 --> 00:35:01,070
Yes.

472
00:35:03,739 --> 00:35:06,079
There is a blanket over there.

473
00:35:06,079 --> 00:35:08,239
- You can go there and...
- Oh, no.

474
00:35:08,309 --> 00:35:11,280
It's so late already. I have to go.

475
00:35:12,750 --> 00:35:13,750
Are you...

476
00:35:15,349 --> 00:35:16,750
Are you leaving?

477
00:35:19,820 --> 00:35:22,190
Of course you should go.

478
00:35:23,190 --> 00:35:26,329
It's way past the time
you're supposed to leave.

479
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:28,869
Of course you should leave.

480
00:35:33,769 --> 00:35:34,840
Secretary Jeong.

481
00:35:37,710 --> 00:35:38,769
Yes, sir.

482
00:35:39,309 --> 00:35:42,480
It's late. Take a taxi home.

483
00:35:43,579 --> 00:35:45,650
It's okay, sir.
I have a long way to go.

484
00:35:45,820 --> 00:35:47,079
Just do it.

485
00:35:48,050 --> 00:35:50,619
- You don't have to worry about...
- Of course I'm worried about you.

486
00:35:51,090 --> 00:35:52,559
Can't you see me?

487
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:55,989
Without you, I have no idea
if I'm talking to a human, a monkey,

488
00:35:56,659 --> 00:35:58,090
a goblin, or a ghost.

489
00:36:04,699 --> 00:36:05,769
Take a taxi home.

490
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:09,769
If something happens to you,

491
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:13,280
I will have no one...

492
00:36:14,940 --> 00:36:16,510
beside me.

493
00:36:26,460 --> 00:36:28,690
Jung Hee! Nam Hee!

494
00:36:31,590 --> 00:36:32,630
I'm sorry.

495
00:36:32,860 --> 00:36:33,929
I can explain why I'm late.

496
00:36:33,929 --> 00:36:35,360
I'm sure something happened
to your boss.

497
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:37,929
And you lost track of time
while handling the situation.

498
00:36:39,070 --> 00:36:40,099
Thank you.

499
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:42,739
Although my legs can't rest,
my mouth can rest...

500
00:36:42,739 --> 00:36:43,869
thanks to you two.

501
00:36:48,949 --> 00:36:50,010
Here you go.

502
00:36:51,179 --> 00:36:52,210
What is it?

503
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:56,320
Since you're going abroad, I got you
a present. With a sim card in it,

504
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:58,289
you can use it
in foreign countries too.

505
00:36:58,650 --> 00:37:01,260
Give me the old one
and take this.

506
00:37:01,260 --> 00:37:02,389
Yes!

507
00:37:13,369 --> 00:37:16,739
Gal Hee, don't you shed
a single tear drop.

508
00:37:17,570 --> 00:37:19,010
Crying in the airport.

509
00:37:19,179 --> 00:37:21,010
That's what people who haven't
been on an airplane do.

510
00:37:21,309 --> 00:37:22,449
Nam Hee!

511
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:27,820
Go see the big world
I haven't seen.

512
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:28,880
Be the master, not the slave.

513
00:37:28,989 --> 00:37:30,320
Be the upper class,
not the lower class.

514
00:37:30,849 --> 00:37:32,690
You have to return home in glory
as a heroine.

515
00:37:35,989 --> 00:37:37,389
Say bye to Mom.

516
00:37:37,389 --> 00:37:39,199
Stop imagining things.

517
00:37:39,199 --> 00:37:40,730
Mom is not here.

518
00:37:40,730 --> 00:37:42,369
Just because we can't see her
doesn't mean she's not here.

519
00:37:42,570 --> 00:37:43,969
Are you saying...

520
00:37:43,969 --> 00:37:46,769
Mom, us, and everyone
doesn't exist to him?

521
00:37:50,909 --> 00:37:54,639
Mom is always watching us
wherever we are.

522
00:37:55,309 --> 00:37:58,610
So say bye to her before you leave.

523
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:14,829
I'm not good at saying goodbye.

524
00:38:16,199 --> 00:38:17,300
Let's just say bye here.

525
00:38:18,699 --> 00:38:20,869
Gal Hee, listen to me.

526
00:38:21,369 --> 00:38:23,070
The people who have belittled you...

527
00:38:23,570 --> 00:38:24,909
and harassed you.

